{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ead469c6-cc09-47df-917a-c420de2c7612","content":"Yes, you'll hit **target framework compatibility issues**. MSTest v3 drops support for:\n\n- **`net5.0`** — .NET 5 is out of support; you must use **.NET 6+**\n- **`net462`** — .NET Framework older than **4.6.2** is dropped (yours is exactly 4.6.2, so it's borderline — but confirm your actual minimum)\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — .NET Core 3.1 is no longer supported; use **.NET 6+**\n\n### What you need to do\n\nUpdate your `TargetFrameworks` before (or as part of) the migration. A typical replacement would be:\n\n```xml\n<TargetFrameworks>net8.0;net462</TargetFrameworks>\n```\n\n- Replace `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` with `net8.0` (or `net6.0` minimum).\n- `net462` is the minimum supported .NET Framework version in MSTest v3.\n\n### Other potential issues\n\n- **`Assert.AreEqual` / `Assert.AreNotEqual`** overload resolution may break if you use `object` comparisons (new generic overloads change resolution).\n- **`DataRow` constructors** — if you pass arrays or complex types, review for breaking changes.\n- **`.testsettings`** files are no longer supported — migrate to `.runsettings`.\n\nWould you like me to perform the full migration on this project?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4a219743-5138-4cc8-8096-224ef999f53f","outputTokens":361,"requestId":"B82C:310A41:E749E7:F52745:6A044E01"},"id":"5b8b6a34-592c-4e1e-9bc4-a1467421c451","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:10:19.662Z","parentId":"da7830f0-557f-4d29-97b0-8c27bdeecc5c"}
